00:14:37.133 --> 00:14:38.267
It's very easy.

00:14:38.267 --> 00:14:40.067
It's very, uh--
It's not prone to bugs.

00:14:40.067 --> 00:14:42.467
But it doesn't always work
for all cases

00:14:42.467 --> 00:14:43.968
in a dynamic application.

00:14:43.968 --> 00:14:46.167
So we're giving you
the developer

00:14:46.167 --> 00:14:49.434
a, uh, imperative way
to tell it what to do

00:14:49.434 --> 00:14:50.968
through something we call
VoxScript.

00:14:50.968 --> 00:14:53.667
VoxScripts are, uh,
just JavaScript

00:14:53.667 --> 00:14:56.968
written against
a very simple API

00:14:56.968 --> 00:14:59.534
that lets you tell the
screen reader what to do.

00:14:59.534 --> 00:15:02.000
