00:42:36.934 --> 00:42:39.367
So, um, to summarize,

00:42:39.367 --> 00:42:41.000
there are some key things
that you can do

00:42:41.000 --> 00:42:42.734
to make your applications
accessible.

00:42:42.734 --> 00:42:45.434
One is to just make sure you
understand your users

00:42:45.434 --> 00:42:48.267
and the use cases under which
they'll be using your products.

00:42:48.267 --> 00:42:50.801
Um, focus on mating--
making products

00:42:50.801 --> 00:42:53.467
that enable independence
and have multiple

00:42:53.467 --> 00:42:55.701
ways of interacting so that
you don't end up relying

00:42:55.701 --> 00:42:58.167
on one method
like using a mouse.

00:42:58.167 --> 00:42:59.534
That you have
redundant methods

00:42:59.534 --> 00:43:01.100
like using a keyboard.

00:43:01.100 --> 00:43:03.367
Um, make sure that
you provide good feedback

00:43:03.367 --> 00:43:05.534
in your applications
so that your users

00:43:05.534 --> 00:43:07.801
know where they are
at all times.

00:43:07.801 --> 00:43:10.934
And also, think of your entire
end-to-end experience

00:43:10.934 --> 00:43:13.467
from the moment they log in
or even browse your pro--

00:43:13.467 --> 00:43:16.067
Like, to browse your website
to learn about your product,

00:43:16.067 --> 00:43:18.133
to the point where
they're setting it up

00:43:18.133 --> 00:43:20.133
using the settings and,
uh,

00:43:20.133 --> 00:43:22.200
looking up documentation.

