00:43:26.767 --> 00:43:28.133
great accessibility built in.

00:43:28.133 --> 00:43:29.234
Use them.

00:43:29.234 --> 00:43:31.033
There's a couple things
that, uh--

00:43:31.033 --> 00:43:32.334
We want to make sure
the biggest thing

00:43:32.334 --> 00:43:33.834
you could do is to make sure
that your application

00:43:33.834 --> 00:43:36.033
can be used by
the keyboard alone

00:43:36.033 --> 00:43:38.567
if it's a web app,
or can be focused and used

00:43:38.567 --> 00:43:42.234
by a trackpad or a roller ball

00:43:42.234 --> 00:43:44.934
if it's a mobile application.

00:43:44.934 --> 00:43:46.767
Uh, I want to make sure
that I'm handling

00:43:46.767 --> 00:43:50.100
tab and focus events properly,
whether I'm in Android

00:43:50.100 --> 00:43:51.634
or on the web.

00:43:51.634 --> 00:43:53.968
And then test it in
the type of accessibility

00:43:53.968 --> 00:43:55.300
technology that
you want to target.

00:43:55.300 --> 00:43:58.367
So download ChromeVox and try
your application out.

